node.text:
In this video we discuss how you can stay motivated as a business owner.

I get questions a lot about this and I wanted to share this with you. 

This is a zoom call that I did live with my students so they could hop on and ask questions.

We do these calls once a month and they’re completely free for the members of the course.

#motivationalwords #motivationalvibes #motivationvideos #motivationalquotesoftheday #motivationmafia #blackwealth

node.title: Staying Motivated As A Business Owner

node.text:
You can flip Pokémon cards for profit! I purchased these from a local card shop, these booster boxes have a promo card inside that is in every single box, if it’s graded and comes back mint It sells for $100+ worst case I make my money back, best case I profit $1500+ on the rare card I have a chance to find inside

node.title: Take that $600 and start a business

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Feldon Richards - iPhone Fix on July 17, 2021 tagging @thebrandstartup, @officialblackwallstreet, @julia_aless, and @blackwealthrenaissance. May be an image of 1 person, standing, car and outdoors.

node.text:
2nd car purchased in the last 2 weeks. Let’s talk about It.

So we drove out to Poughkeepsie, Ny today and we grabbed a 2013 Ford Focus with 130K miles. Why?

Swipe to learn more!

The plan is to start a rental car business and buy additional cars every 3 months. This one was just to get our foot in the door.

I made about $10k last week fixing and flipping phones, so i needed to do something productive with the money so I don’t waste It 😂.

Will keep you guys posted on the journey, but we are just getting started. Started in the projects, it’s a process. It ain’t perfect, but this is progress! 🔥 had to sneak a lil bar in there 😂. 

If you enjoyed this post, save It, share It, drop a comment. Let me know. I’m always getting into something to make some extra bread so if you really wanna show love make sure you follow me @nycphonebuyer for side hustle tips.

Thanks for putting me on game @julia_aless 

#rentalcar #rentalcars #turo #lyft #uber #hyrecar #rentalproperties #fixandflip #cardeals #carflipping #phoneflipping #sidehustles

node.text:
I’m just a regular dude makin irregular moves.

2014 bankrupt, lost my car, no sleep, hospital, same year got my bank job.

2017 lost family member, manager was a dick so I side hustled quit.

2020 pandemic, lost 6 figures, made It back, moved out the projects.

With adversity comes opportunity.

We all got a purpose. I believe mine is to show you all that no matter what obstacles come your way, you can overcome them as long as you back up your faith with hard work.

In the last slide, you’ll see my sales for last month flipping and fixing iPhones. 

My hustle paid for my whip. 

I hope I inspire someone today, because it’s only up from here!

For those that don’t know yet, I run an at home cell phone repair business. I didn’t go to school for this and had no prior experience when I started 4 years ago. I’ve taught over 7k people how to start this side hustle with less than $100 and my goal is to double that by the end of the year. 

I love getting messages from people telling me I changed their life with my program, and I wanna let you know that your kind words have changed mine. Y’all inspire me to keep going even when times get hard. 🔥 

This year is your year. Drop a 💯 to affirm. Hit my dm with any questions.

Save this post and share It!

Follow @nycphonebuyer to learn how to start a phone repair business with $100 or less.

node.text:
Read👇🏿 Focus on what you can do now, not later.

When you do take action, make sure you give yourself positive reinforcement. You’re no good to yourself if you don’t know how to talk to yourself.

Make a plan and stick to It.
Whatever situation you’re in right now will not change without your interference.

There’s always an opportunity to get better. I didn’t enjoy my job at the bank because after a couple of promotions I realized the corporate world was not for me. 

Initially, I felt like I had to change my appearance to fit some mold they thought I should have, but eventually I realized It would be best to start my own journey and live life on my own terms.

Regardless of where you are financially, make sure you put health, family, and peace first. If your mind, body and relationships are not right then It will be difficult for you to focus on anything else. Get healthy before the money.

A couple days ago, I made almost $1000 in profit repairing phones. It took me years to get to this point, but I am here now and I love It.

We have a one week vacation planned this month where we are flying out for a week and another trip planned next month with the family.

This is why I do what I do. I do It for the freedom. I don’t mind working, but when I had a job I couldn’t go on vacation every month. I only got 4 weeks out of the year. Don’t let me or anyone else make you feel bad about working though. I am just sharing my experience. I know plenty of people with jobs they love, but even more that have jobs they hate, so I am talking to you. 

I am here to let you know that you decide what happens next. No one else. You. 
Not your bills. Not your boss. Not your parents. Not your spouse. Not your ex. Not your kids. 

You.

node.text:
That’s how It went down 😂 I would never get my boy a sammysung.

We tried everything: otter box, screen protectors, cases, but none of that worked.

Then, I started to hold him accountable. I told him one day that if he’s going to keep breaking them, then HE would need to learn to fix them. So daddy went first, of course.

I learned, then I taught my 8 year old how to do It too. It was intimidating at first, but I’ve done more complicated things in my life like trying to put a car seat into a car. No kidding! Car seat installation is a blow 😂

So 4 years later, here we are. 6 figure phone repair business from home, thousands of students, changing lives all over the world. All because my son broke his iPhone. I tell people all the time, most of my successes in life didn’t happen by accident but they were inspired by one.

Don’t be discouraged to try something new because you think it’s too hard for you. Be willing to challenge yourself daily!

Follow @nycphonebuyer to learn dope side hustles that make money outside the 9-5 ‼️

node.text:
Success requires a mindset shift. You have to admit to yourself that your current situation is a result of what you tolerate.

This is a hard pill to swallow for most. Most people believe that the world is out to get them and the odds are stacked against them. 

The truth is, something is out to get all of us, it’s called life. There’s no escape.

We’ve all got bills to pay, and responsibilities. Some obligations. Your struggle isn’t special, it’s just unique. There will be similarities in everyone’s journey, but no ones path is exactly the same.

Stop letting people and things control your life. The goal? Work hard enough to make a living but not so much that you don’t enjoy life.

If you’re unhappy now, then change your environment.

If it’s stress related to money, then stop wasting your money and start investing It and making It work for you.

Your money is a symbol of your life energy. Treat It as such.

node.text:
Excuses don’t pay the bills.

Working a full time job with 2 kids and building a business was not easy, but I got It done, why? Because I told myself I had to.

Initially, I had to break my old bad habits: Netflix, partying, traveling, etc.

Let’s stop lying to ourselves about what we deserve and start focusing on what we earn.

I used to believe that I deserved a week vacation to relax because I worked hard on the job. Really though? Do you? I mean everyone else is doing that too.

What’s the difference between deserving and earning? Well, we all deserve a break, so no one ends up getting It except the people that EARN It.

With a few exceptions, we are all born with the same option to succeed. With options comes responsibility. It’s up to you to choose the path you take.

Now if you have a job, you deserve a break, but you’ve got to earn It. How? Take the money you earn at work and put It to work for you. 

Make your money work hard so you can take It easy. That’s how you earn your freedom. That’s how I earned mine.

I wish everyone could relax all day and take It easy, but wishes don’t pay the bills either. Hustle hard fam!
